\f0\fs24 \cf0 1. When editing this map in Omnigraffle, make sure to add a URL action in the \'93Properties\'94 section of the \'93Inspect\'94 sidebar. For the URL, write the prefix \f1\b l.dv/ \f0\b0 (which will later be expanded to a list of channel name results on LIGO-DV-Web) followed by the partial channel name (should look like \f1\b l.dv/<channel-name> \f0\b0 )\ 2. Run the \f1\b add_ligo_dv_links.sh \f0\b0 script (full text below) on this graffle file. For example, if the SVG file is called \f1\b map.svg \f0\b0 , you would run \
\f1\b ./add_ligo_dv_links.sh map.svg \f0\b0 .\ 3. Re-open this file and confirm that any new links have been expanded properly.\ 4. Export to your preferred format. SVG, PDF, and HTML all preserve links.\ \ Full text of \f1\b add_ligo_dv_links.sh \f0\b0 (note that the \f1\b sed \f0\b0 command is a single line):\ \
\f1\b #!/bin/sh\ \ sed -i.orig 's|l.dv/\\([a-zA-Z0-9_-]*\\):\\([a-zA-Z0-9_-]*\\)|https\\://ldvw.ligo.caltech.edu/ldvw/view?act=baseChan\\&baseSelector=true\\&ifo=any\\&subsys=any\\&fsCmp=%3E%3D\\&fs=any\\&chnamefilt=\\1%3A\\2\\&currentOnly=show+only+currently+acquired\\&submitAct=Retrieve+Channel+List+%BB|g' "$1"}

For example, this comparator would have channel names beginning with: \ \pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\f2\i0\b \cf0 H1:SYS-TIMING_Y_FO_A_PORT_9_SLAVE_CFC \f0\i \ \ \pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\b0 \cf0 While onsite, use the \f1\i0 sitemap \f0\i command from any terminal to view a menu of MEDM control screens. Click \i0 SYS > Timing \i to get a \'93green screen\'94 real time view of the timing system.\ \ Use \f1\i0 dataviewer \f0\i from any terminal to get timeseries data on any of these channels. Go to the \i0 Signal \i tab, select the \i0 Slow \i checkbox in the bottom left corner, and navigate through \i0 H1 > H1:SYS > H1:SYS-TIMING \i and so on until you\'92ve found the relevant channel. All possible channels are listed, regardless of whether they are in active use.}
